\strong{Dynamic warning levels.}
Enhanced scores are assigned to five levels (0--4) using quantile
breakpoints at the 40th, 60th, 80th, and 95th percentiles of the
nonzero score distribution:
\itemize{
\item Level 0 (\code{"none"}) -- score is zero.
\item Level 1 (\code{"low"}) -- score \eqn{\le} 40th percentile.
\item Level 2 (\code{"moderate"}) -- score \eqn{\le} 60th percentile.
\item Level 3 (\code{"high"}) -- score \eqn{\le} 80th percentile.
\item Level 4 (\code{"critical"}) -- score > 95th percentile.
